# Offline-First Standards

This document defines patterns for building mobile applications that work reliably without network connectivity. All features that persist or sync data must follow these standards.

---

## Sync Strategy Selection

### Strategy Comparison

| Strategy | Use Case | Conflict Risk | Complexity | Examples |
|----------|----------|---------------|------------|----------|
| Last-Write-Wins (LWW) | Single-user, low conflict | Low | Low | Settings, preferences |
| CRDT | Multi-user, real-time collab | High | High | Collaborative docs |
| Operational Transform (OT) | Multi-user, ordered ops | Medium | High | Text editing |
| Merge by timestamp | Single-user, infrequent sync | Low | Low | Notes, todos |
| Server authoritative | Financial, compliance | N/A | Low | Transactions |

### Selection Checklist

- [ ] Identify conflict scenarios (same record edited on multiple devices)
- [ ] Choose strategy based on conflict frequency and data criticality
- [ ] Document chosen strategy in architecture
- [ ] LWW is default for single-user apps; justify if using CRDT/OT

---

## Last-Write-Wins Implementation

### Requirements

- [ ] Every syncable entity has `updated_at` (ISO 8601 UTC)
- [ ] Client sends full record with timestamp on sync
- [ ] Server compares timestamps; newer wins
- [ ] Deleted records use tombstone with `deleted_at` timestamp
- [ ] Tombstones retained for sync window (e.g., 30 days)

### Example Schema

```json
{
  "id": "rec_abc123",
  "updated_at": "2025-02-26T14:30:00Z",
  "deleted_at": null,
  "data": { ... }
}
```

### Conflict Handling

```python
def merge_lww(local: Record, remote: Record) -> Record:
    """Last-write-wins merge. Returns the record with later updated_at."""
    if remote.get("deleted_at") and local.get("deleted_at"):
        return remote if remote["updated_at"] > local["updated_at"] else local
    if remote.get("deleted_at"):
        return remote  # Deletion wins if newer
    if local.get("deleted_at"):
        return local
    return remote if remote["updated_at"] >= local["updated_at"] else local
```

