## CRDT (Conflict-free Replicated Data Types)

### When to Use

- Real-time collaboration (multiple users editing same document)
- Offline edits that must merge without server arbitration
- Order-independent collections (sets, maps)

### Common CRDTs

| Type | Use Case | Library/Reference |
|------|----------|-------------------|
| LWW-Element-Set | Unique items with timestamps | Yjs, Automerge |
| RGA (Replicated Growable Array) | Ordered lists | Yjs |
| LWW-Map | Key-value with last-write per key | Automerge |
| G-Counter | Increment-only counters | Standard |

### Implementation Notes

- [ ] Use established libraries (Yjs, Automerge) rather than custom CRDTs
- [ ] Document which CRDT type is used for each entity
- [ ] Test merge behavior with concurrent edits
- [ ] Consider size growth (CRDT metadata can accumulate)

---

## Operational Transforms (OT)

### When to Use

- Rich text editing with multiple cursors
- Ordered operations where sequence matters
- When CRDT is not available for the data model

### Requirements

- [ ] OT server must be authoritative for conflict resolution
- [ ] Client buffers operations when offline
- [ ] Rebase/transform on reconnect
- [ ] Document OT algorithm and version

---

## Queue Management

### Offline Queue

- [ ] All mutating operations go through a queue when offline
- [ ] Queue persists to local storage (survives app restart)
- [ ] Queue is processed in order when connection restored
- [ ] Failed operations are retried with backoff (exponential)
- [ ] Max retries with dead-letter or user notification

### Queue Implementation Pattern

```python
class OfflineQueue:
    def enqueue(self, op: Operation) -> None:
        """Add operation to queue. Persist immediately."""
        self.storage.append(op)
        self.persist()

    async def process(self) -> None:
        """Process queue when online. Stop on first failure."""
        while self.queue and self.is_online():
            op = self.queue[0]
            try:
                await self.execute(op)
                self.queue.pop(0)
                self.persist()
            except RetryableError:
                op.retry_count += 1
                if op.retry_count >= MAX_RETRIES:
                    self.dead_letter(op)
                break
```

### Queue Limits

| Item | Limit | Action when exceeded |
|------|-------|--------|
| Queue size | 1000 ops | Block new ops or drop oldest |
| Single op size | 100 KB | Reject or chunk |
| Stale ops | 7 days | Discard or flag for user |

