## Optimistic UI

### Principles

- [ ] UI updates immediately on user action
- [ ] Pending state is visually indicated (e.g., dimmed, spinner)
- [ ] Rollback on failure with user notification
- [ ] Rollback restores previous state correctly

### Implementation

```typescript
// Optimistic update pattern
async function updateItem(item: Item) {
  const previous = getItem(item.id);
  setItem(item);  // Optimistic UI update
  setPending(item.id, true);

  try {
    await syncAPI.update(item);
  } catch (e) {
    setItem(previous);  // Rollback
    showError("Could not save. Changes reverted.");
  } finally {
    setPending(item.id, false);
  }
}
```

### Rollback Requirements

- [ ] Previous state is stored before optimistic update
- [ ] Rollback is atomic (all or nothing for related updates)
- [ ] User is informed when rollback occurs
- [ ] Conflict resolution does not silently overwrite user intent

---

## Conflict Resolution

### User-Facing Conflicts

When automatic merge is not possible (e.g., LWW with user-critical data):

- [ ] Present both versions to user
- [ ] Allow "Keep mine" / "Keep theirs" / "Merge manually"
- [ ] Store resolution for audit
- [ ] Do not lose data; preserve both until resolved

### Conflict Notification

- [ ] User is notified when conflict is detected
- [ ] Notification is non-blocking but visible
- [ ] Resolution flow is accessible from notification
- [ ] Unresolved conflicts are surfaced in settings or dashboard

